From: Yu Kuai <yukuai3@huawei.com>
Date: Mon, 30 Jan 2023 09:41:36 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] block, bfq: fix uaf for bfqq in bic_set_bfqq()
Git-commit: b600de2d7d3a16f9007fad1bdae82a3951a26af2
Patch-mainline: v6.2-rc7
References: bsc#1251201 CVE-2022-50488

After commit 64dc8c732f5c ("block, bfq: fix possible uaf for 'bfqq->bic'"),
bic->bfqq will be accessed in bic_set_bfqq(), however, in some context
bic->bfqq will be freed, and bic_set_bfqq() is called with the freed
bic->bfqq.

Fix the problem by always freeing bfqq after bic_set_bfqq().

(Coly Li: rebased for Linux v5.14 based SUSE kernel)

Fixes: 64dc8c732f5c ("block, bfq: fix possible uaf for 'bfqq->bic'")
Reported-and-tested-by: Shinichiro Kawasaki <shinichiro.kawasaki@wdc.com>
Signed-off-by: Yu Kuai <yukuai3@huawei.com>
Reviewed-by: Jan Kara <jack@suse.cz>
Link: https://lore.kernel.org/r/20230130014136.591038-1-yukuai1@huaweicloud.com
Signed-off-by: Jens Axboe <axboe@kernel.dk>
Signed-off-by: Coly Li <colyli@suse.de>

---
 block/bfq-iosched.c |    4 +++-
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/block/bfq-iosched.c
+++ b/block/bfq-iosched.c
@@ -5058,9 +5058,11 @@ static void bfq_check_ioprio_change(stru
 
 	bfqq = bic_to_bfqq(bic, false);
 	if (bfqq) {
-		bfq_release_process_ref(bfqd, bfqq);
+		struct bfq_queue *old_bfqq = bfqq;
+
 		bfqq = bfq_get_queue(bfqd, bio, BLK_RW_ASYNC, bic);
 		bic_set_bfqq(bic, bfqq, false);
+		bfq_release_process_ref(bfqd, old_bfqq);
 	}
 
 	bfqq = bic_to_bfqq(bic, true);
